<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The fellowship is basic Gandalf. Bid 0 or 1. If you win, choose second to give yourself more time to get Gandalf. In case you didn&#39;t catch on, everybody is Gandalf Signets except Gandalf. This means Gandalf&#39;s Wisdom works on everybody. It&#39;s not always game winning, but a -1 (or -2 if you have 2) can add up with a lot of possessions. The strategy is pumping your guys so they don&#39;t lose skirmishes. Even with the errata, Trust Me is still useful and can be game winning. <br>
Shadow is your basic Nazgul. I have won many times at site 3 or 4 with this deck. If they bid too high, Toldea and Enquea wreck them. Too Great and Terrible puts a hurt on Gandalf. I would normally play 2, but Gandalf based decks aren&#39;t too popular in my area. The Pale Blade wrecks condition dependent decks as The Witch King with Blade usually wins. Cantea gets rid of pesky Nazgul Hate weapons like Flaming Brands and well you should know how the basic Nazgul strategy works.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
